    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For the Android folks coming here for Kotlin</p>\n\n<pre><code>val dirtyString = \"\uD83D\uDCB0 Account Balance: $-12,345.67\"\nval cleanString = dirtyString.replace(\"[^\\\\d.]\".toRegex(), \"\")\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>Output:</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>cleanString = \"12345.67\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><em>This could then be safely converted <code>toDouble()</code>, <code>toFloat()</code> or <code>toInt()</code> if needed</em></p>\n"
